solution.p:
 Let's name g(x)=x^{1/3}. Then g'(x)=\dfrac{1}{3} x^{-2/3}
and g''(x)=-\dfrac{2}{9} x^{-5/3}. In particular, g(8)=2,
g'(8)=\dfrac{1}{12}, and g''(x) \lt 0 for all x \gt 0.

Set f(x)=\arctan(x). Then f'(x)=\dfrac{1}{1+x^2}, so
f'(1)=\dfrac{1}{2} and

f(1.1)\approx f(1)+f'(1)(1.1-1)=\frac{\pi}{4}+\frac{1}{20}

ul.li:
 When 1\leq c\leq2, we know that 18 \leq 22-c^2 \leq 21, and that numerator and denominator are non-negative, so


\left|\frac{c}{6(22-c^2)}\right|
  &=\frac{c}{6(22-c^2)}
  \leq \frac{2}{6(22-c^2)}  \leq \frac{2}{6\cdot 18}

  & = \frac{1}{54} \leq \frac{1}{50}


as required.

