 When 0 \lt  c \lt 1, we know that 1 \gt  e^{-c}  \gt  e^{-1} and
8 \leq 8+c^2  \lt  9, so


\left|\frac{e^{-c}}{6(8+c^2)}\right|
  &=\frac{e^{-c}}{6(8+c^2)}

  &  \lt  \frac{1}{6 |8+c^2|}

  &  \lt  \frac{1}{6\times 8} = \frac{1}{48}  \lt  \frac{1}{40}


as required.

